"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-31-swimmers-slap-a-race-olympics-21334944\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Swimming, on paper at least, looks a relatively straightforward sport - but viewers tuning in from the comfort of their own homesoften have plenty of questions.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Swimming\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"paper\", \"from\": 13, \"to\": 18}, {\"ngram\": \"a relatively straightforward sport\", \"from\": 35, \"to\": 69}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 83}, {\"ngram\": \"the comfort\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 110}, {\"ngram\": \"their own homesoften\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 134}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 140, \"to\": 146}, {\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And chief amongst them is why on Earth some swimmers slap themselves before the start of a race.\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"chief\", \"from\": 166, \"to\": 171}, {\"ngram\": \"Earth\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 200}, {\"ngram\": \"some swimmers\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 214}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such is the force that the swimmers hit themselves with, that red marks are sometimes visible on an athlete's body afterwards.\", \"from\": 260, \"to\": 386, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the force\", \"from\": 268, \"to\": 277}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 295}, {\"ngram\": \"red marks\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 331}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's body\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 374}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris Olympics 2024 So, why exactly do swimmers, such as those competing at theOlympics, turn their force on their own bodies?\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 567, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 418}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 430}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"why exactly do swimmers\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympics\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 527}, {\"ngram\": \"their force\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"their own bodies\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 565}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is everything you need to know.\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 587}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some swimmers chose to slap themselves before a race in order to increase blood flow to certain muscles, which in turn helps with performance.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some swimmers\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 620}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 668}, {\"ngram\": \"blood flow\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 691}, {\"ngram\": \"certain muscles\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 710}, {\"ngram\": \"turn\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The shoulders, biceps, triceps and pectorals are essential for swimming so athletes will usually start with these areas.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The shoulders\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"biceps\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 772}, {\"ngram\": \"triceps\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"pectorals\", \"from\": 786, \"to\": 795}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"these areas\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legs are typically next to receive the treatment, with the thighs and hamstrings next to benefit from the increased blood flow.\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 1004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The legs\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 881}, {\"ngram\": \"the treatment\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"the thighs\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"hamstrings\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"the increased blood flow\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 1003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, there is a psychological aspect, too.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a psychological aspect\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Barbini, USA's director of performance, previously toldTODAYthat it helps to keep athletes calm and composed whilst they are waiting for the race to get underway.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1221, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1068, \"end\": 1071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999669339966609, \"rank\": 2.2663159298751e-05, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Matt Barbini\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1149}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbini said: 'Anything that sort of kills those in-between moments before the race starts, I think helps keep athletes calm and it helps to distract them from the nerves.'\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1395, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Barbini\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1230}, {\"ngram\": \"Anything\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1246}, {\"ngram\": \"that sort\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"those in-between moments\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1306}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"the nerves\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The thinking behind this is that, faced with a long wait on the starting blocks before the start of the race, the act of hitting themselves helps to stave away pressure and thoughts of self-doubt.\", \"from\": 1397, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The thinking\", \"from\": 1397, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"a long wait\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"the starting blocks\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"the act\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1514}, {\"ngram\": \"pressure\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"thoughts\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1578}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also been said that a swimmer hitting themselves pre-race is an act of intimidation to their competitors, with loud slapping a display of intimidating and threatening behaviour.\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 1777, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a swimmer\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1629}, {\"ngram\": \"pre\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1657}, {\"ngram\": \"an act\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"intimidation\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"their competitors\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1704}, {\"ngram\": \"a display\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"behaviour\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1776}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not every swimmer slaps their body before a race though - every athlete has their own individual pre-race routine.\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1893, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Not every swimmer\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"their body\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1813}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1827}, {\"ngram\": \"every athlete\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1850}, {\"ngram\": \"their own individual pre-race routine\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1892}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But for those athletes who do hit themselves, they are unlikely to change their routine - especially if they keep on winning.\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 2020, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those athletes\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"their routine\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:How Andy Murray and Dan Evans 'transformed' into Olympic medal contenders ArrowMORE:How South Korea's Kim Yeji became the ultimate Olympics fashion icon ArrowMORE:Remarkable moment a bee nearly ruins archers' gold medal hopes at Olympics Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2036, \"end\": 2047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6654281274814414e-23, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2121, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9974377306109088, \"rank\": 0.002492813702901548, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2135, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.7290634430916418, \"rank\": 0.21978095046557797, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 2139, \"end\": 2143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"score\": 0.9999999998835847, \"rank\": 1.1642874822730957e-10, \"text\": \"Yeji\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", 